definition.value: The human placenta is hemomonochorial, as this membrane consists of a single layer of synctiotrophoblast at term. In mice maternal blood bathes a perforated layer of cytotrophoblast cells that overlay two layers of syncytiotrophoblast, thus the murine placenta is hemotrichorial. Maternal blood has direct access to the murine synctiotrophoblast layer I via fenestrations in the murine cytotrophoblast layer.

In mice maternal blood bathes a perforated layer of cytotrophoblast cells that overlay two layers of syncytiotrophoblast, thus the murine placenta is hemotrichorial. Maternal blood has direct access to the murine synctiotrophoblast layer I via fenestrations in the murine cytotrophoblast layer.
